This paper is about recommendation systems, which typically fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The use of embedding models and matrix factorization also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The incorporation of contextual constraints may also relate to social and information networks (cs.SI) or natural language processing (cs.CL) depending on the specific application.
